dc_title_s: Poland 1:100,000. Czestochowa, sheet R-13. A.M.S. M651 (G.S.G.S. 4416)
dc_description_s: AMS 2. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4416. Alternate title: Czestochowa, Poland. Polyconic projection. Russian belt 4 grid. Relief shown by 10 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. With a glossary. Compiled from Germany 1:25,000, German General Staff, 1883-1929; Germany 1:100,000, German General Staff, sheet 106, 1938; Poland, 1:100,000, Military Geographic Institute, sheets 44-27, 1935; 44-28, 1934; 45-27, 1933 and 45-28, 1933. Road classification in Poland based on British intelligence reports, 1943.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
